# Curriculum vitae

maree.carroll [ at ] gmail.com

Melbourne, Victoria, Australia

## Qualifications

* 2004 Bachelor of Information Technology @ Queensland University of Technology
  - Double Major: Software Engineering/ Data Communications
  - Course GPA: 6.0 (scale 1-7, 7 highest)

* 2016 currently completing Masters Comp Sci @ RMIT University
  - Specialising in Big Data
  - Course GPA: 3.5 (scale 1-4, 4 highest)

* Data science MOOCs

## Skillset

### Software engineering
* Agile / Lean methodology (/ 'Hybrid' methodology)
* continuous integration / jenkins / TDD

### Data science

* Big data
  - Data Mining / Machine Learning
  - Hadoop / MapReduce
  - Cloud computing / AWS / Google / IBM Bluemix

* Real world clients in Agriculture, Energy and other industry sectors
  - Weather and climate time series data analysis
  - decision-support insight from data

### Web development
* Node.js / React / Stylus / Bootstrap / CSS3 / HTML5
* MongoDB / InfluxDB / MySQL
* PHP  5 / Laravel 

### Python

* 10 years experience
* pandas / numpy / scipy / sklearn

## Work History

* 2012 - current 
  - Web development, software development and data science roles in public sector
  - Python, PHP, Perl, Java, J2EE, C, C++ across a range of platforms
  - client liasion

## Ambitions

To apply and broaden my skill set and experience, with enthusiasm to learn new things, to any situation and achieve quality results. To work in a team, or as an individual, with a mixture of a strong work ethic, a goal-oriented approach, and a sense of humour, to ultimately produce products and/or services of high standard.

I am driven to always do a high standard of work, focused foremost on client needs, whether that be an effective web application, software that drives value or reproducible data science that finds insight from data.

## Referees

Referees can be provided on request
